  "text": "In the large majority of cases (90%), volvulus complicating intestinal malrotation occurs in the first year of life, even in the first months (66-80%), respectively. [CITATION_1] This is the reason why some authors propose a prophylactic Ladd's procedure consisting in the lysis of the Ladd's bands, enlarging the mesenteric base and repositioning of the intestine. [CITATION_2] While the procedure is commonly accepted in the context of acute volvulus treatment, its indication as a prophylactic procedure in asymptomatic patients is highly controversial. Indeed, a recent study suggests higher morbidity and mortality at subsequent admission in operated patients. [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] In our case, operation indication was guided by the clinical complaints of the infant.",
